        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(i18n): add Hebrew (he) locale",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw had no Hebrew (`he`) locale. Hebrew users got the English Control UI and no Hebrew docs.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nRegisters `he` end-to-end so the existing automated translation pipeline (Control UI locale refresh + docs `translate-all`) generates and maintains Hebrew like every other locale. Contributors only prepare the locale; org-side automation does the translation.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Hebrew appears in the Control UI language switcher and loads as a lazy locale bundle.\n- Browser language `he` (and legacy `iw`) auto-resolves to Hebrew.\n- RTL renders automatically (existing `detectTextDirection` already handles the Hebrew script).\n- Docs translation will produce Hebrew pages once `he` is added to the publish-repo matrix (`openclaw/docs`).\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Wiring: `ui/src/i18n/lib/types.ts`, `registry.ts` (lazy loader + `resolveNavigatorLocale`), `scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts`, `control-ui-i18n-report.ts`, language label in `en.ts`.\n- Pipeline: `he` added to the `control-ui-locale-refresh.yml` matrix so CI auto-translates with the org key; placeholder `he.ts` generated via the standard generator (English fallback, marked pending).\n- Docs: `docs/.i18n/glossary.he.json` + `he-navigation.json`.\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check` → `he: clean` (all locales clean).\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts` → 11/11 passing (`he` added to structural parity coverage).\n- `pnpm --dir ui build` → succeeds; emits separate `he-*.js` chunk.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "feat/i18n-hebrew-locale",
